name: Naomi Davis
tweet: @Lleyn_Birding If you, a person, killed a bat you would be committing a wildlife crime. I don't understand how letting repeat feline offenders continue to maim and kill bats is any less of a crime. A dog kills a lamb and it gets shot, but a cat can wipe out a roost and *nothing happens*.

name: Andrew Clarke
tweet: @NaturNaomi Bats are fascinating animals and I respect all who monitor, appreciate and care for them (I co-founded a local bat group years ago). But I’d rather see a domestic cat eat the odd bat (and other wildlife) than seeing one kept indoors and fed a diet of eg factory-farmed chicken.

name: Naomi Davis
tweet: I am a volunteer bat carer. I pay for their care, their medicine, their rehab. 50% of my bats are attack victims. So when you tell me it's "too hard" to keep your PET animal indoors and entertained enough to stop it consistently killing wildlife?? You can fuck off.
